<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="20">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="20">
Burgess (1989: 249) recognized three species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1B16E22-5503-46E3-8E9E-EF7935778506" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim Cuvier 1829:293" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sorubim</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lima">S. lima</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A2A5765C-1874-47F8-8E96-370ED77701AC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim latirostris Miranda-Ribeiro 1920:14" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latirostris">S. latirostris</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A87E9236-71E1-4887-B166-A0CDAC6A56F3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim trigonocephalus Miranda-Ribeiro 1920:12" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trigonocephalus">S. trigonocephalus</taxonomicName>
, and reported 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lima">S. lima</taxonomicName>
as “occasionally seen” in the aquarium hobby. Herein, and in earlier publications describing species (Littmann et al. 2000; 2001a; 2001b), I conclude that five species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1B16E22-5503-46E3-8E9E-EF7935778506" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim Cuvier 1829:293" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sorubim</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed from morphological characters, and that at least three of the species, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lima">S. lima</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DE2E6A95-A91F-4F1F-9601-3F2A40F90C42" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim elongatus Littmann, Burr, Schmidt &amp; Isern 2001:4" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">S. elongatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:744184CA-9548-4EDA-A96E-751728A9A1E1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim maniradii Littmann, Burr &amp; Buitrago-Suarez 2001:88" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maniradii">S. maniradii</taxonomicName>
are syntopic. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lima">Sorubim lima</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DE2E6A95-A91F-4F1F-9601-3F2A40F90C42" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim elongatus Littmann, Burr, Schmidt &amp; Isern 2001:4" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">S. elongatus</taxonomicName>
are commonly seen in the aquarium trade. These taxonomic conclusions have significant implications for both the ornamental and commercial fishing industries in South America, especially because catch data have not recognized multiple species and consequently have confused the potential differential impact of ornamental, commercial, and subsistence fishing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="21" pageNumber="20">
Commercial fishing within South America is severely limited in that several populations are under-fished (see Littmann et al. 2000) and potential harvests are seemingly unlimited. In addition, there is a need to identify harvested fishes (such as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1B16E22-5503-46E3-8E9E-EF7935778506" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim Cuvier 1829:293" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sorubim</taxonomicName>
), which are not as popular as some of the other food fishes more frequently reported on throughout the Amazon region (
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DA6C0802-488B-47D3-BF11-04F139848EBF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serrasalmidae" genus="Colossoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Colossoma Eigenmann &amp; Kennedy 1903:530" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Colossoma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6A022164-0B29-4FAD-AE58-3BD690F83322" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Brachyplatystoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Brachyplatystoma Bleeker 1862:10" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Brachyplatystoma</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:45767C01-E3E4-4254-A94A-EB05C7980D6A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Arapaimidae" genus="Arapaima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Arapaima Müller 1843:326" order="Osteoglossiformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Arapaima</taxonomicName>
). For example, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3551D3F9-5069-42B9-AED3-3EA5E8B8A80D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim cuspicaudus Littmann, Burr &amp; Nass 2000:903" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cuspicaudus">Sorubim cuspicaudus</taxonomicName>
occurred in over 40% of the collections at 29 sampling sites in the Magdalena River floodplain system (Kapetsky et al. 1977). Other authors refer to 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lima">S. lima</taxonomicName>
as a highly significant component of the fishery in the La Plata system (Quiros &amp; Cuch 1989) as well. Overfishing of popular fish species (e.g., 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Pseudoplatystoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatum">Pseudoplatystoma fasciatum</taxonomicName>
) continues at seemingly alarming rates (see Kapetsky et al. 1977, Littmann et al. 2000). Perhaps in the future, regulations put on fisherman and their harvests may cause a trickle-down effect, forcing them to target less frequently captured species, such as species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1B16E22-5503-46E3-8E9E-EF7935778506" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim Cuvier 1829:293" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sorubim</taxonomicName>
and other underutilized, fisheries taxa. For this reason, life history and population ecology studies of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1B16E22-5503-46E3-8E9E-EF7935778506" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Sorubim" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Sorubim Cuvier 1829:293" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sorubim</taxonomicName>
are urgently needed.
</paragraph>
